    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is accepted based on: (1) the ASTM F1717 protocol specifies a single standardized test condition; (2) analytical sensitivity analysis confirms model predictions are insensitive to loading rate over the quasi-static regime; (3) medium model risk level does not require full multi-condition characterization. Overall credibility is sufficient to support the regulatory submission decision for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
